# Toolkit v2 WebAuthn action API smoke.

The real browser ceremony needs a user gesture and a real/stubbed
`navigator.credentials`; unit coverage exercises that runtime path. This
conformance case keeps the public `.ssc` API importable and constructible on the
portable lanes.

[signal](std/ui/primitives.ssc)
[webauthnRegister, webauthnAssert](std/ui/webauthn.ssc)

```scalascript
val result = signal("waResult", "")
val error  = signal("waError", "")

val register = webauthnRegister("/webauthn/enrol/begin", "/webauthn/enrol/complete",
  "ScalaScript demo", result, error)
val assertPasskey = webauthnAssert("/webauthn/signin/begin", "/webauthn/signin/complete",
  result, error)

println("webauthn-actions:" + (result() == "") + ":" + (error() == ""))
```
